candidates.title: Move procfs-specific code into optional module
candidates.body: Making procfs support optional lets us build a "pure" filtering version of Laurel for debugging purposes or for running in non-auditd-plugin setups.

candidates.title: Restart laurel on SIGHUP
candidates.body:
When we catch SIGHUP, all remaining input in the buffer is fed to coalesce, coalesce is flushed. Laurel is restarted with identical configuration parameters and capabilities.

Implements part of #133

candidates.title: Update dependencies, add Cargo.lock
candidates.body: Goal Keep laurel buildable with Rust 1.56

candidates.title: Replace custom syslog code with log crate
candidates.body: Both syslog and console output is generated

candidates.title: Refine data types
candidates.body:
Since keys are short, there's no need to use references from the input buffer. This lets us get rid of PKey, RKey. The most common keys are encoded in a Common variant.

Value::Map now uses newly introduced SimpleKey and SimpleValue types.
